  {
   "question": "Where does Shadow Priest Phase 4 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 305 top-ranked Shadow Priest DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 4 (Zul'Aman), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Shadow Priest items in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Bracers of Nimble Thought (99%), Shroud of Absolution (97%), Handguards of Absolution (94%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Zul'Aman."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Shadow Priest use in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Runed Living Ruby in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Shadow Priest need in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "10 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Power on head, Greater Inscription of Discipline on shoulders, Runic Spellthread on legs and Enchant Weapon - Soulfrost on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Power comes from Almaador — Shattrath City."
